High School: A 2008 graduate of Central Catholic HS in Modesto, Calif…team posted a 23-3-1 overall record during his final two seasons…played on the offensive and defensive lines where he helped the squad to a pair of Sac-Joaquin Section titles…Central Catholic also became the first Sac-Joaquin Section team to compete in a state title game when it faced St. Bonaventure for the Div. III championship in 2007…as a junior, he had 43 tackles, including one sack…had at least one tackle in every game…recorded seven stops against Ripon HS for his season high…made 79 tackles as a senior…that total included 8.5 sacks…had at least five tackles in 12 of the team’s 14 games…tied his career high with eight tackles against Amador…also had 3.5 sacks in that game. Personal: A business administration major…parents are Richard and Nancy Lawrence.}
